ologous to zero. Moreover, the (full) Erd\\H{o}s-P\\'osa property holds for\n$S_1$-$S_2$-cycles and cycles not homologous to zero on an orientable surface.\nFinally, we also describe the canonical obstructions to the Erd\\H{o}s-P\\'osa\nproperty for cycles not homologous to zero and for odd $S$-cycles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 May 2016 16:34:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 6 Jul 2016 13:52:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 28 Feb 2017 16:04:06 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 7 Apr 2017 14:01:54 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 28 Mar 2019 14:53:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-29"}
